{
  "texts": [
    "Suppose a given model is found to be able to realize any possible labeling of an available training set.",
    "Then, reasonably one would not expect the model to learn meaningful insights from the training data.",
    "It is plausible that some form of learning may still occur, albeit without a clear understanding of the underlying mechanisms.",
    "However, under such circumstances, uniform generalization bounds would inevitably become trivial.Theorem 1.",
    "(Finite sample expressivity of quantum circuits)."
  ]
}